<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-20T09:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-20T09:36:00-05:00" n="859" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/133</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-20T08:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1916, 8 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A decree September 15 gives banks sixty days to cover their bills with
                            metallic reserves. Vera Cruz banks now closed. Decree sent by next
                            mail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>